				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">@Bregalad: Just curious, how many metasprite frames do you have and how much data is there?   Are you finding trading time for space savings to be a win?   It almost seems to be worth encoding the mirrored versions of the metasprites rather than doing the mirroring in code?<br /><br />What I ended up doing was having a separate page for static data like metasprites.  Each sprite in the metasprite takes up 4 bytes that match the OAM layout  (delta y, palette mask, index, delta x) in order to trade size for speed.<br />Mirrors are encoded instead of computed.  Each frame of body animation has socket locations for arms and head so the character can aim in any directions for any frame of animation.  I need to take a second pass over the main character to get a smoother run sequence so I'm revisiting my scheme.  I think I'll need to make a tool for metasprite layout (so far I've been doing it by hand.)</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

